#What this does

#When Docker builds an image, it sends all project files to the Docker daemon as a "build context."
# Without this file, it would send node_modules/ (potentially hundreds of MB), 
#your .env credentials, and files that aren't needed inside the container. 
#This keeps the context small and prevents secrets from leaking into image layers.

node_modules/
frontend/node_modules/
.git/
.env
*.md
Makefile
sql/
.gitignore
docker-compose.yml
Dockerfile
nginx/default.conf
